metadata.name: Rebirth
metadata.description:
Lava from Kilauea Volcano flowing into the Pacific Ocean at dusk on the East Shore of the island of Hawai`i in the district of Puna, November 28th 2016. As the molten lava flows into the cool ocean, new land is born, and the island grows in size until the pounding surf collapses the lava bench, and the cycle starts anew. 

Aia lā ‘o Pele i Hawai‘i ‘eā
Ke ha‘a mai lā i Maukele ‘eā
‘Ūhī‘ūhā mai ana ‘eā
Ke nome a‘e lā iā Puna, ‘eā
‘Owaka i ka lani, nokenoke
Ē Pele ē Pele ē.

Pele is in Hawai‘i
She is dancing at Maukele
She rumbles and mutters
As she consumes Puna.
Flashing in the heavens, on and on
O Pele, Pele.

- Kumu Hula Tutu Mae L. Loebenstein
